// compiler/codegen/plugin_attr_scaffold.hexa — RFC 070 G7-D.scaffold marker
//
// @cite RFC 070 §3.B fat-.so single-symbol convention
// @cite RFC 070 §3.C capability gate
// @cite RFC 070 §3.D ABI version stamp
// @cite RFC 070 §4.6.1 design decision LOCKED: (A) @plugin(capabilities=[...]) in-source
// @cite RFC 070 §4.6.2 fixed 12-byte ABI stamp record layout
// @cite RFC 070 §4.6.3 zero behavior change this commit
//
// STATUS: SCAFFOLD MARKER ONLY (G7-D.scaffold sub-cycle).
//   Header-comment-only file documenting where G7-D.impl will hook into the
//   existing codegen pipeline. Zero code, zero behavior change.
//
// This file exists to lock the integration shape so that G7-D.impl's PR is
// small + reviewable + obviously bounded.

// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// G7-D.impl integration plan — three hooks
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// 1) compiler/parser — attribute parser extension
//    File: self/codegen_c2.hexa (or wherever @cite/@stability are recognised
//          in the deployed driver; verify at G7-D.impl start)
//    Change: extend the attribute-arglist parser to accept `string[]` for the
//            `capabilities` named arg of `@plugin(...)`.
//    Today: @cite("...") and @stability("phase-a") accept ONE string. The
//           grammar `@<name>(<key> = <expr>)` needs `<expr>` to admit a
//           string-array literal.
//    Backward compat: zero — `@plugin` is currently unrecognised, so any
//           today-legal source remains today-legal.
//    Test: parse `@plugin(capabilities = ["a", "b"])` -> AST node with
//          name="plugin", args=[("capabilities", StringArrayLit(["a","b"]))].
//
// 2) compiler/codegen — section emit
//    Files: compiler/codegen/arm64_darwin.hexa  (Mach-O)
//           compiler/codegen/x86_64_linux.hexa  (ELF)
//    Change: when emitting an `.so`/.dylib (G7-A/B path, i.e. `bopts[4]=="1"`
//            per RFC 070 §4.3) for a translation unit that contains a fn
//            with `@plugin(capabilities=[...])`, emit TWO custom sections:
//
//      (a) __HEXA,__abi  (Mach-O) / .hexa.abi  (ELF) — fixed 12 B LE record
//          (u32 runtime_version, u64 nanbox_layout_hash) per §4.6.2.
//          - runtime_version source = self/runtime.c::HEXA_RUNTIME_VERSION
//            (read by compiler at build time; baked into rodata).
//          - nanbox_layout_hash source = compiler-computed SHA-256[0..8] over
//            canonical NanBox tag literal + payload sizeof list.
//
//      (b) __HEXA,__cap  (Mach-O) / .hexa.cap  (ELF) — HXC v2 payload encoding
//          CapManifest{ plugin_id, capabilities[] (sorted), rfc_version=1,
//          compiler_id } per §3.C + §4.6.2 schema.
//          - plugin_id derived from the `@plugin`-annotated fn name minus the
//            "_dispatch" suffix.
//          - capabilities[] verbatim from the attribute arglist, sorted asc
//            for byte-determinism per F-D2 contract.
//          - HXC v2 encoder source = stdlib/hxc/ (already exists per @D g_hxc).
//
//    Mach-O details: extend the existing `__TEXT`/`__DATA` section emit path
//      to add custom `__HEXA` segment with two sections. Section header bytes
//      = 80 B per section (Apple `<mach-o/loader.h>` `struct section_64`).
//      Update `MH_DYLIB` load command count (LC_SEGMENT_64 segcount).
//    ELF details: extend the existing `.text`/`.rodata` section emit path to
//      add two SHF_ALLOC sections at sh_type = SHT_PROGBITS with names from
//      the section-name string table.
//
// 3) self/runtime.{c,h} — host-side gate wire
//    File: self/runtime.c (the dlopen FFI consumer; today calls libc dlopen
//          directly per RFC 070 §2 audit list)
//    Change: when `hexa_dlopen` (G7-C entry) lands, prepend a call to
//            `stdlib/dynlink_caps.hexa::dynlink_full_gate` BEFORE the libc
//            `dlopen`. On gate-fail: do NOT call libc dlopen; surface the
//            gate's dlerror string verbatim to `hexa_dlerror`.
//    Backward compat: today there is no `hexa_dlopen` wrapper, so this is a
//            net-new code path; existing raw-FFI dlopen consumers (per §2
//            audit) are NOT redirected through the gate — they remain raw
//            consumers of libc dlopen unless/until they migrate to
//            `hexa_dlopen` (G7-C decision, not G7-D scope).
//
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// What this scaffold file is NOT
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
//   - NOT a codegen entry point. compiler/main.hexa does not import this.
//   - NOT parsed as Hexa code beyond the file header (zero declarations).
//     A pure comment-only `.hexa` file is currently parsed as an empty
//     translation unit; this is intentional (zero behavior change).
//   - NOT a substitute for the real impl in arm64_darwin.hexa /
//     x86_64_linux.hexa — those files are where the actual section-emit
//     logic will live at G7-D.impl. This file is a planning marker that
//     G7-D.impl will reference + then delete (or fold into a per-target
//     header comment, mirroring RFC 070 §4.4 G7-A.native scaffold pattern).
//
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Cross-references
// ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
//   - §4.4 G7-A.native scaffold — same Shape-B "comment-only marker before
//     impl" pattern; this file mirrors that approach for the G7-D side.
//   - stdlib/dynlink_caps.hexa — companion skeleton (host-side gate fn
//     shells); together these two files lock the G7-D shape end-to-end.
//   - @D g3 real-limits-first — F-D1 anchored on nanbox ABI invariant;
//     F-D2 anchored on least-privilege contract. See RFC 070 §4.6.4.
//   - @D g5 hexa-native-only — section emit lives in compiler/codegen
//     hexa-side (not in clang flags). The C-path fallback (clang -shared)
//     will NOT receive these sections in G7-D.impl phase 1 — that path
//     stays "F-A1 PASS, F-A2/F-D1/F-D2 EXPECTED-FAIL" until / unless a
//     follow-up cycle adds a `--cap-manifest=<.tape>` clang invocation.
//     (This is consistent with §4.5's honest scoping of the C path as
//     "functionally correct, ABI-noisy".)
//   - @D g_hxc — CapManifest payload uses HXC v2; ABI stamp does NOT
//     (fixed 12 B for dependency-free verification per §4.6.2).
